         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Kew Nov. 1/63. ¶ My dear Mueller ¶  ¶ I have several letters to acknowledge &amp; to thank you for, but a series of heavy domestic afflictions in my own &amp; my wife's family ¶  have thrown much sorrow &amp; muc...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">63.11.01</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS black-edged.</p>
               </note>Kew Nov. 1/63.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have several letters to acknowledge &amp; to thank you for, but a series of heavy domestic afflictions in my own &amp; my wife's family<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Hooker's father-in-law, J. S. Henslow, died in May 1861; his niece, Anne McGilvray, aged 11, in August 1862; then in 1863 a favourite Aunt Henslow, eldest sister of Hooker's wife Frances, followed by his own daughter, Maria Elizabeth (Minnie) on 28 September 1863, aged six. See Allan (1967), passim.</p>
               </note> have thrown much sorrow &amp; much business on my hands. Nor am I yet free, as my eldest boy<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">William Henslow Hooker.</p>
               </note> is just recovering from scarlet fever, &amp; my mother is lying now ill with the same. My father happily is perfectly well.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was grieved to hear of the damp having got to your returned collections,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to W. Hooker, 8 June 1863.</p>
               </note> &amp; can assure you that this must have happened after they left the Herbarium; we have no damp room in the whole house, none that are not full of plants, &amp; I saw your collections packed in a perfectly dry state. I have shown your letter to Bentham &amp; Black &amp; Helmsly<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Allan Black, Hemsley?</p>
               </note> who assisted in the packing; &amp; they truly observe, that if packed damp here, they would have reached you hopelessly rotted &amp; past doing any-thing with — As it is I am excessively sorry for it, as there is nothing we can do but pack them in tin, in a perfectly dry state.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I should have sent you the enclosed<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Not identified.</p>
               </note> a month ago, but have been quite thrown off my work.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham is progressing with the <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> &amp; has got past the <name key="Genisteae">Genisteae</name> &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am busy with the New Zealand Flora,<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1864-7).</p>
               </note>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but have done very little to it for 2 months. The Phanogamic part is however nearly finished — Gen Plant.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83).</p>
               </note> is not quite at a stand still, for Bentham is at the <name key="Leguminosae">Leguminosae</name> for it, &amp; I have done <name key="Rosaceae">Rosaceae</name>, Saxif.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <name key="Saxifrageae">Saxifrageae</name>.</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Lythrarieae">Lythrarieae</name>, Onagrar.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <name key="Onagrarieae">Onagrarieae</name>.</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Drosereae">Drosereae</name>,<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Droseraceae.</p>
               </note> Combret.,<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <name key="Combretaceae">Combretaceae</name>.</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Rhizophoreae">Rhizophoreae</name>, &amp; <name key="Halorageae">Halorageae</name> &amp; allied orders, so that some progress is made you see.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My Father desires his kindest regards.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Do you take the "Natural History Review" it is becoming a standard work, &amp; contains a long Review of the Australian Flora, in the October number.<note xml:id="ftn13" type="footnote" n="13">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Included in a general discussion of the Colonial Floras project, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Natural history review</seg>, vol. 3, 1863, pp. 497-507. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever most sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D Hooker</p>
